TEXT.TITLE: VICTORIA STATE BANK ISSUES 50 MLN AUS DLR EUROBOND
TEXT.BODY: The State Bank of Victoria is raising 50 mln Australian dlrs through a three-year bullet eurobond at 14-1/2 pct and priced at 101-3/8, lead and sole manager Commerzbank AG said. The bond is due on May 15, 1990 and interest is paid on that date annually. Payment date is also May 15. Denominations are 1,000 and 10,000 dlrs and listing is in London. Fees total 1-1/2 pct, with a half-point for management and underwriting and one point for selling. REUTER
